{"lemma":"مَسْخَةٍ","slug":"مَسْخَةٍ","root":"م.س.خ","root_slug":"م-س-خ","root_link":"/words/roots/م-س-خ","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مَسْخ","root":"مسخ","pos":"V","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n38578"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%B3%D9%92%D8%AE%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to transform, transmute, change into something else"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to distort, spoil"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Hebrew מַסֵּכָה (masekhá, “molten image”)."},"ipa":["/ma.sa.xa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n38578","headword_ar":"مَسَخَهُ","root":"msx","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masoxN","text_ar":"مَسْخٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He transformed him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"metamorphosed him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into a worse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"more foul,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"more ugly, shape."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) Ex."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masaxahu A@ll~`hu qirodFA","text_ar":"مَسَخَهُ ا@للّٰهُ قِرْدًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God transformed him into an ape."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) [See Kur, xxxvi. 67.] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masaxa $iEorFA","text_ar":"مَسَخَ شِعْرًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He took and transformed poetry;"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to the most common usage,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by the substitution of what is synonymous with the original, wholly"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"partly;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but sometimes"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by altering the meanings."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, F.) See 1 (last sentence) in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"slx","text_ar":"سلخ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masaxa AlkaAtibu","text_ar":"مَسَخَ الكَاتِبُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The writer corrupted what he wrote by changing the diacritical points and altering the meaning."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masaxa Aln~aAqapa","text_ar":"مَسَخَ النَّاقَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masoxN","text_ar":"مَسْخٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He rendered the she-camel lean, and wounded her back, by fatigue and use:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A'Obeyd, L, K:) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masaHa","text_ar":"مَسَحَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masuxa","text_ar":"مَسُخَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masaAxapN","text_ar":"مَسَاخَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(flesh-meat, and fruit,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, tasteless,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"insipid: it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(food)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had no salt nor colour nor taste:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and, sometimes,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it was between sweet and bitter."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masaxa TaEomahu","text_ar":"مَسَخَ طَعْمَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It caused its taste to depart; took away its taste."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","Msb","L"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}